2. Content-Type restriction bypass

👉 Meaning:
Server checks file type using HTTP header:

Content-Type: image/jpeg

👉 Problem:
Server trusts this header (which attacker can fake)

👉 What you did:

Sent PHP file but changed header to image/jpeg
Server accepted it

👉 Result:
✔ Malicious file uploaded → RCE
